message.content:
1. Mean VAS scores in the first 30 min of post-operative period were significantly lower in groups BK1 and BK2.
2. Mean VAS scores in the first 30 min of post-operative period were higher in groups other than BK1 and BK2.
3. Total analgesic consumption in the first 24 h of post-operative period was significantly lower in groups BK1 and BK2.
4. Total analgesic consumption in the first 24 h of post-operative period was higher in groups other than BK1 and BK2.
5. The differences in mean VAS scores and total analgesic consumption were statistically significant (P < 0.05).
